I"-<h1 id="general-features">General Features</h1>

<p>Buildfarm has endeavored to support a wide variety of features implied or mandated by the Remote Execution API, including those currently not in use or worked around by bazel or other clients.</p>

<p>Most notably, buildfarm has universal support for:</p>

<ul>
  <li>configurable instances with specific instance types</li>
  <li>progressive and flow controlled CAS reads and writes</li>
  <li>pluggable external CAS endpoints</li>
  <li>RequestMetadata behavior attribution</li>
</ul>

<p>Bazel Client Feature Usage:</p>

<h2 id="fetch-api---planned"><a href="https://docs.bazel.build/versions/master/command-line-reference.html#flag--experimental_remote_downloader">Fetch API</a> - <a href="https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel-buildfarm/pull/605">Planned</a></h2>
